compute an estimate of $\Vert x\Vert_0$ that is accurate within a factor
$1\pm\beta$, plus an additive error $O(\log^3(u)\varepsilon^{-2}\beta^{-2})$,
with high probability, and 2) For every $H\sim\mathcal{H}$, $Hx + \varphi$ is
$\varepsilon$-differentially private over the randomness in $\varphi$.
