vertex cover problem on graphs with maximum degree 3 to obtain a substantially
faster 6/5-approximation algorithm than the one currently known. We complement
our positive, upper bound results with negative, lower bound results which
prove that the problem of designing good advice for greedy is computationally
hard and even hard to approximate on various classes of graphs. These results
significantly improve on such previously known hardness results. Moreover,
these results suggest that obtaining the upper bound results on the design and
analysis of greedy advice is non-trivial.
